text:

title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - 4th Street

text:
(1) 359 King's Highway, at the N.E. corner of West 4th Street, showing the old Stillwell house, which was occupied by G. Stillwell in 1857.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing a rear view from West 3rd Street.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing the east side of the house.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, south from Quentin Road to King's Highway, showing West 4th Street, and a rear view of the Stillwell house. The row of 2-story brick fronts are on the south side of King's Highway, between West 4th and 5th Streets.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
